illiam Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1930.1|1930}}\n| {{sort|Murder at the Vicarage|''The Murder at the Vicarage''}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Marple|[[Miss Marple]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Giant's Bread]]''\n| {{sort|1930.2|1930}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1930.2|1930}}\n| ''Giant's Bread''\n| [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]]\n| Other\n| As Mary Westmacott\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Floating Admiral|''[[The Floating Admiral]]''}}\n| {{sort|1931.1|1931}}\n| [[Hodder & Stoughton]]\n| {{sort|1932.1|1932}}\n| {{sort|Floating Admiral|''The Floating Admiral''}}\n| [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]]\n| Mystery novel\n| With members of [[Detection Club|The Detection Club]].<ref name=\"BL: Floating Admiral\" />{{efn|A chapter each was completed by: Canon [[Victor Whitechurch]], [[G. D. H. Cole|George]] and [[Margaret Cole]], [[Sir Henry Aubrey-Fletcher, 6th Baronet|Henry Wade]], [[Agatha Christie]], [[John Rhode]], [[Milward Kennedy]], Sayers, [[Ronald Knox]], [[Freeman Wills Crofts]], [[Edgar Jepson]], [[Clemence Dane]] and [[Anthony Berkeley]]. [[G. K. Chesterton]] contributed the prologue.<ref name=\"BL: Floating Admiral\" />}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Sittaford Mystery|''[[The Sittaford Mystery]]''}}\n| {{sort|1931.2|1931}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1931|1931}}\n| {{sort|Murder at Hazelmoor|''The Murder at Hazelmoor''}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| Mystery novel\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Peril at End House]]''\n| {{sort|1932|1932}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1932.2|1932}}\n| ''Peril at End House''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Lord Edgware Dies]]''\n| {{sort|1933|1933}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1933|1933}}\n| ''Thirteen at Dinner''\n| [[Do