irot]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Pocket Full of Rye|''[[A Pocket Full of Rye]]''}}\n| {{sort|1953.2|1953}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1954|1954}}\n| {{sort|Pocket Full of Rye|''A Pocket Full of Rye''}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Marple|[[Miss Marple]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Destination Unknown (novel)|Destination Unknown]]''\n| {{sort|1954|1954}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1955.2|1955}}\n| ''So Many Steps to Death''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]. Syndicated in US Newspapers as ''Destination X''.\n| Mystery novel\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Hickory Dickory Dock (novel)|Hickory Dickory Dock]]''\n| {{sort|1955|1955}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1955.1|1955}}\n| ''Hickory Dickory Death''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Dead Man's Folly]]''\n| {{sort|1956.1|1956}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1956|1956}}\n| ''Dead Man's Folly''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Burden|''[[The Burden]]''}}\n| {{sort|1956.2|1956}}\n| [[Heinemann (publisher)|Heinemann]]\n| {{sort|1963.1|1963}}\n| {{sort|Burden|''The Burden''}}\n| [[Dell Publishing]]\n| Other\n| As Mary Westmacott\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[4.50 from Paddington]]''\n| {{sort|1957|1957}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1957|1957}}\n| ''What Mrs. McGillicuddy Saw!''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Marple|[[Miss Marple]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Ordeal by Innocence]]''\n| {{sort|1958|1958}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1959|1959}}\n| ''Ordeal by Innocence''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| Mystery novel\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope