cule Poirot stories#Colonel Race|Colonel Race]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Hollow|''[[The Hollow]]''}}\n| {{sort|1946|1946}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1946|1946}}\n| {{sort|Hollow|''The Hollow''}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Taken at the Flood]]''\n| {{sort|1948.1|1948}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1948.1|1948}}\n| ''There is a Tide . . .''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Rose and the Yew Tree|''[[The Rose and the Yew Tree]]''}}\n| {{sort|1948.2|1948}}\n| [[Heinemann (publisher)|Heinemann]]\n| {{sort|1948.2|1948}}\n| {{sort|Rose and the Yew Tree|''The Rose and the Yew Tree''}}\n| [[Rinehart & Company]]\n| Other\n| As Mary Westmacott\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Crooked House]]''\n| {{sort|1949|1949}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1949|1949}}\n| ''Crooked House''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| Mystery novel\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Murder is Announced|''[[A Murder Is Announced]]''}}\n| {{sort|1950|1950}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1950|1950}}\n| {{sort|Murder is Announced|''A Murder Is Announced''}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Marple|[[Miss Marple]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[They Came to Baghdad]]''\n| {{sort|1951|1951}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1951|1951}}\n| ''They Came to Baghdad''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| Mystery novel\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Mrs McGinty's Dead]]''\n| {{sort|1952.1|1952}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|1952.1|1952}}\n| ''Mrs McGinty's Dead''\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"