 stories, in chronological order by UK publication date, even when the book was published first in the US or serialised in a magazine in advance of publication in book form.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|+ Christie's short-story collections\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 13em;\"| UK title<ref name=\"Gage CA\" />{{sfn|Dalby|2004|pp=32\u201338}}{{sfn|Keating|1988|pp=68\u201371}}\n! scope=\"col\"| Year of UK<br />publication\n! scope=\"col\"| UK publisher<br />(All London)\n! scope=\"col\"| US title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year of US<br />publication\n! scope=\"col\"| US publisher<br />(All New York)\n! scope=\"col\"| Series\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Poirot Investigates]]''\n| {{sort|1924|1924}}\n| [[John Lane (publisher)|John Lane]]\n| ''Poirot Investigates''\n| {{sort|1925|1925}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Partners in Crime (short story collection)|Partners in Crime]]''\n| {{sort|1929.1|1929}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| ''Partners in Crime''\n| {{sort|1929|1929}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| [[Tommy and Tuppence]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sort|Mysterious Mr Quin|''[[The Mysterious Mr Quin]]''}}\n| {{sort|1930|1930}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|Mysterious Mr Quin|''The Mysterious Mr Quin''}}\n| {{sort|1930|1930}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Quin|[[Harley Quin]]}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sort|Thirteen Problems|''[[The Thirteen Problems]]''}}{{efn|An abridged edition was published as ''The Mystery of the Blue Geraniums, and Other Tuesday Club Murders'' by [[Bantam Books]] in 1940.{{sfn|Dalby|2004|pp=32\u201338}}}}\n| {{sort|1932|1932}}\n| [[William Collins, Sons|William Collins & Sons]]\n| {{sort|Tuesday Club Murders|''The Tuesday Club Murders''}}\n| {{sort|1933|1933}}\n| [[Dodd, Mead and Company|Dodd, Mead & Co]]\n| {{sort|Marpl