\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n| ''[[The Harlequin Tea Set]]''\n| {{sort|1997|1997}}\n| [[G. P. Putnam's Sons]]\n| \u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[The Big Four (novel)|The Big Four]] (short-story version)'' <ref name=\"harpercollins.com.au\">[http://www.harpercollins.com.au/9780008165000/#sm.00001luqhn2eqmfl4qhm3qzq0mf69 Original 12-part short-story version]</ref>''\n| {{sort|2017|2017}}\n| [[Harper Collins]]\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n| {{sort|Poirot|[[Hercule Poirot]]}}\n|}\n\n===List of short stories===\nA total of 165 stories have been written and published in 15 collections in the US and the UK.<ref>{{cite web| title=Agatha Christie reading order with dates| url=http://uk.agathachristie.com/attachments/assets/Reading_order_with_dates.pdf| publisher=Agatha Christie Official UK Site| accessdate=23 September 2013| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110919221400/http://uk.agathachristie.com/attachments/assets/Reading_order_with_dates.pdf| archivedate=19 September 2011| df=dmy-all}}</ref> 164 stories were published in the UK with the omission of \"Three Blind Mice\". The original short stories that were used for [[The Big Four (novel)|''The Big Four'']] were published in 2017. 152 stories were published in the US with the omission of \"Christmas Adventure\", which was the original version of \"The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding\". Some stories were published under different names in the US collections.\n\nFour short stories\u2014\"The Submarine Plans\", \"Christmas Adventure\", \"The Mystery of the Baghdad Chest\", and \"The Second Gong\"\u2014were expanded into longer stories by Christie (respectively \"The Incredible Theft\", \"The Adventure of the Christmas Pudding\", \"The Mystery of the Spanish Chest\" and \"Dead Man's Mirror\"). All four of the original versions were published in the UK, and three of them were published in the US (with \"Christmas Adventure\" being the exception).\n\n====UK collections====\nThis is a list of 165 stories sorted by the 15 UK collections in chronological order.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%\"\n!style=\"width:20%\" scope=col|UK collection\n!style=\"width:40%\" scope=col|UK title\n!style=\"width:40%\" scope=col|US collection\n|-\n!rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:center\" scope=\"row\"|''[[Poirot Investigates]]'' (11){{sfn|Fitzgibbon|1980|p=83}}\n||\"The Adventure of 'The Western Star'\"||rowspan=\"11\"|''[[Poirot Investigates]]'' (14)\u2014also includes \"The Veiled Lady\", \"The Lost Mine\", and \"The Chocolate Box\"{{sfn|Fitzgibbon|1980|p=83}}\n|-\n|\"The Tragedy at Marsdon Manor\"\n|-\n|\"The Adventure of the Cheap Flat\"\n|-\n|\"The Mystery of Hunter's Lodge\"\n|-\n|\"The Million Dollar Bond Robbery\"\n|-\n|\"The Adventure of the Egyptian Tomb\"\n|-\n|\"The Jewel Robbery at the Grand Metropolitan\"\n|-\n|\"The Kidnapped Prime Minister\"\n|-\n|\"The Disappearance of Mr. Davenheim\"\n|-\n|\"The Adventure of the Italian Nobleman\"\n|-\n|\"The Case of the Missing Will\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"15\" style=\"text-align:center\" scope=row|''[[Partners in Crime (short story collection)|Partners in Crime]]'' (15){{sfn|Fitzgibbon|1980|pp=91\u201392}}\n||\"A Fairy in the Flat\"||rowspan=\"15\"|''[[Partners in Crime (short story collection)|Partners in Crime]]''{{sfn|Fitzgibbon|1980|pp=91\u201392}}\n|-\n|\"A Pot of Tea\"\n|-\n|\"The Affair of the Pink Pearl\"\n|-\n|\"The Adventure of the Sinister Stranger\"\n|-\n|\"Finessing the King/The Gentleman Dressed in Newspaper\"\n|-\n|\"The Case of the Missing Lady\"\n|-\n|\"Blindman's Buff\"\n|-\n|\"The Man in the Mist\"\n|-\n|\"The Crackler\"\n|-\n|\"The Sunningdale Mystery\"\n|-\n|\"The House of Lurking Death\"\n|-\n|\"The Unbreakable Alibi\"\n|-\n|\"The Clergyman's Daughter/The Red House\"\n|-\n|\"The Ambassador's Boots\"\n|-\n|\"The Man Who Was No. 16\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"12\" style=\"text-align:center\" scope=\"row\"|''[[The Mysterious Mr Q